Module gaudin.firstscreen
Package model

Class Inventory

java.lang.Object
model.Inventory
public class Inventory extends Object
Defines the Inventory class. The Inventory class has a dependency on the Part and Product classes. It houses methods and Observable Lists that access Parts and Products. FUTURE ENHANCEMENTS. The organization could add an observable list and functions to keep track of company objects and allow the organization to track the companies that make their outsourced parts.

    • lookupPart

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Part> lookupPart(String partName)
      Loads and returns filteredParts. This method adds parts to the Observable list filteredParts if they contain characters that match characters in the string partName. It also clears filteredParts if there are already Part objects in it.
      Parameters:
      partName - the string value to search for.
      Returns:
      an observable list of parts called filteredParts. RUNTIME ERROR. I wrote this without the first if statement originally and this created a logical error returning too many objects. I added the if clause and this fixed the issue.

    • lookupProduct

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Product> lookupProduct(String productName)
      Loads and returns filteredProducts. This method adds products to the Observable list filteredProducts if they contain characters that match characters in the string productName. It also clears filteredProducts if there are already Product objects in it.
      Parameters:
      productName - the string value to search for.
      Returns:
      an observable list of parts called filteredProducts.

    • deletePart

      public static boolean deletePart(Part selectedPart)
      Finds Part in allParts and deletes it. This method loops through the observable list allParts until it finds a matching Part Id then it removes the part in allParts and returns True. If it does not find a matching Id it returns false.
      Parameters:
      selectedPart - the object to search for and remove.
      Returns:
      True or False.
